description:
Repost: @brujafromthebay
⠀
This video shows how @Google manipulates search results to dismiss conspiracy theories. The first results to appear when searching “322 new cases of covid” are articles from mainstream sources debunking the “322 COVID conspiracy” when the word “conspiracy” wasn’t even typed in the search box. These are followed by example after example of news headlines that say “322 new cases” appearing across the US, giving credence to the conspiracy Google is trying to debunk.
⠀
So why 322? I won’t pretend to understand the motives behind a phenomenon like this but I do know that another name for Skull & Bones, one of the three big secret societies at Yale, is Order 322. Perhaps they are hinting as to who is behind this false flag or it’s an inside joke of sorts.
⠀
